4, 11:04 AM UpdatedMay 22, 2024, 09:48 PM PARIS-Drivers and ticket inspectors on Paris commuter trains launched a one-day strike on May 21 to pressure management over bonuses for the Olympics in July and August, leading to criticism of union tactics.\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 457, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3755004113321155e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"AFP PublishedMay\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"11:04 AM\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 384}, {\"ngram\": \"UpdatedMay\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"PARIS-Drivers and ticket inspectors\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"a one-day strike\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 508}, {\"ngram\": \"management\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"bonuses\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 564}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 577, \"to\": 583}, {\"ngram\": \"criticism\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 605}, {\"ngram\": \"union tactics\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Drivers walked off the job on most RER (Reseau Express Regional metro system) and other commuter lines, which are used daily by millions of workers living in the capital's suburbs, causing major delays and huge traffic jams.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_B\", \"score\": 0.6239290455212132, \"rank\": 0.5834172972607528, \"text\": \"RER\", \"types\": [\"Q728937\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RER_B\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Drivers\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"Reseau Express Regional metro system\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"other commuter lines\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's suburbs\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"major delays\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"huge traffic jams\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I left two hours earlier than normal to make sure I was on time,\\\" said restaurant worker Anne-Sophie Collier, who still managed to arrive in central Paris in the morning, but only after an uncomfortable journey on a packed train.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1004, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3755004113321155e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 918}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurant worker Anne-Sophie Collier\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"the morning\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"an uncomfortable journey\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"a packed train\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unions representing workers across the public sector have launched strikes or are threatening to in order to demand extra pay or support for having to work over the July 26-Aug 11 Olympics, which fall during the traditional summer holidays in France.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1329, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999991435051045, \"rank\": 8.544545520109507e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Unions\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"workers\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"the public sector\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"strikes\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"extra pay\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"-Aug\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"the traditional summer holidays\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a heavy workload with 4,500 additional trains in August, so a whole range of our colleagues will not be able to go on holiday,\\\" said a union member.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a heavy workload\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"4,500 additional trains\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1392}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1402}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole range\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"our colleagues\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"holiday\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"a union member\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Police, air traffic controllers, Paris rubbish collectors, central government employees, metro drivers and firefighters have all made pay demands, with the government under pressure to agree to them in order to prevent disruption spoiling the Games.\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1530, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3755004113321155e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"P